Publishes the offline refresh-migration transaction for managed conversations whose mutable active JSONL tail has regrown after activation.

Safety and verification:
- refresh requires all Codex owners to be closed;
- rehydrates exact history and retains the prior generation;
- activates only a strictly smaller candidate around a native checkpoint;
- does not force semantic Compact;
- 31 exported files match the verified source export by SHA-256;
- exported public contract, 21 Rust tests, fmt, strict Clippy, privacy scan, and Markdown-link audit pass.

No new binary release is included. The public CLMSetup alpha does not yet install automatic exit maintenance.
